<exercise checkit-seed="0009" checkit-slug="E3" checkit-title="Solving linear systems">
  <statement>
    <p>
Consider the following 
system of linear equations.n<me>\begin{matrix}
 -x_{1} &amp;  &amp;  &amp;  +  &amp; 3 \, x_{3} &amp; = &amp; -11 \\
 3 \, x_{1} &amp;  +  &amp; x_{2} &amp;  -  &amp; x_{3} &amp; = &amp; 6 \\
 -2 \, x_{1} &amp;  &amp;  &amp;  +  &amp; 5 \, x_{3} &amp; = &amp; -19 \\
 &amp;  &amp;  &amp;  &amp; 2 \, x_{3} &amp; = &amp; -6 \\
 \end{matrix}</me>
    </p>
    <ol>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to find a simpler
          system
          
that has the same solution set.
        </p>
      </li>
      <li>
        <p>
Explain how to find the solution set of this simpler
          system.
          
        </p>
      </li>
    </ol>
  </statement>

  <answer>
      <me>\mathrm{RREF}\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
-1 &amp; 0 &amp; 3 &amp; -11 \\
3 &amp; 1 &amp; -1 &amp; 6 \\
-2 &amp; 0 &amp; 5 &amp; -19 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 2 &amp; -6
\end{array}\right]=\left[\begin{array}{ccc|c}
1 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 2 \\
0 &amp; 1 &amp; 0 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 1 &amp; -3 \\
0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0 &amp; 0
\end{array}\right]</me>
      <p>The solution set is <m> \left\{ \left[\begin{array}{c}
2 \\
-3 \\
-3
\end{array}\right] \,\middle|\,  \in\mathbb R \right\} </m>.</p>
  </answer>
</exercise>
